main event: A pilot and navigator of a United States Navy patrol aircraft observed a bright light moving at a high speed over the Atlantic Ocean on January 8, 1966.
interesting points: The object was estimated to be at an altitude of 10,000-15,000 feet and moving in excess of 1,500 knots., The sighting lasted approximately 30 seconds before the light disappeared., The light appeared very intense and moved at a downward angle., Witnesses described the light as bright and dazzling to the eye., The report contains various analyses and conclusions regarding other sightings that were deemed credible.
witness description: Pilot and navigator of a United States Navy patrol aircraft
